    <section id="design">
      <h2>How the Traffic Is Built and Delivered</h2>
      <p>Understanding how OLSP Solo Ads traffic is sourced and delivered is important for assessing its likely quality and fit for a given buyer's offer. This section covers both the vendor's stated model and the limits of independent verification.</p>

      <h3>Traffic Source (Vendor Claims)</h3>
      <p>Wayne Crowe's team describes the OLSP/Traffic Dominators email lists as being built from paid advertising on Google Ads and Bing Ads, plus organic SEO traffic across Traffic Dominators and OLSP-related properties. The vendor explicitly contrasts this with what they describe as lower-quality solo ad lists built by repeatedly renting or swapping list access with other solo ad providers — a practice associated with list fatigue, where subscribers have been repeatedly pitched the same MMO offers and engagement rates decline. The vendor claim is that building lists from fresh search traffic produces subscribers with higher intent and fewer prior exposures to competing offers.</p>

      <div class="callout info">
        <strong>What this means in practice:</strong> If accurate, search-built lists would theoretically have better engagement than recycled solo ad lists — a meaningful advantage in the saturated MMO/Biz Opp space. Whether the Traffic Dominators list is actually built this way, and to what proportion, cannot be confirmed from any independent public source.
      </div>

      <h3>Delivery Mechanics</h3>
      <p>A solo ad purchase with OLSP works through a straightforward model: the buyer selects a click package and provides a destination URL (an opt-in page, an OLSP Magick Link, or another affiliate offer). Wayne's team writes or uses a promotional email — some packages provide the buyer's own copy, while others use in-house copywriting — and sends the dedicated email to segments of the Traffic Dominators list until the agreed number of clicks is reached. Clicks are tracked against the buyer's URL, and when the click count is fulfilled, the campaign is complete. The buyer typically receives their clicks within a defined window after ordering, though specific delivery timeframes are not prominently documented in public materials.</p>

      <h3>OLSP Ecosystem Integration</h3>
      <p>Inside the OLSP System dashboard, solo ads are accessible through a "traffic" or "traffic toolbox" section, linking members directly to solo ad ordering pages. OLSP's training explicitly recommends using solo ads in combination with the Magick Link (OLSP's tracked referral funnel URL) so that traffic flows into the broader OLSP commission structure — meaning purchases made by leads acquired through solo ads can generate commissions to the OLSP member whose Magick Link was used. The Traffic Rotator product extends this by providing ongoing monthly traffic to a member's Magick Link automatically, rather than requiring individual solo ad purchases.</p>
    </section>

