    <section id="faq">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What exactly does "Tier-1 traffic" mean, and does it guarantee better results?</summary>
        <p>Tier-1 traffic refers to clicks from subscribers in high-income countries — primarily the US, UK, Canada, Australia, and New Zealand. The theory is that these audiences have higher purchasing power and are more likely to convert on MMO/Biz Opp offers than subscribers in developing markets. OLSP Solo Ads markets its traffic as "100% Tier 1." Whether this claim is accurate, and what percentage of actual delivered clicks fall into Tier-1 countries, cannot be confirmed from any independent source. More importantly, Tier-1 traffic is a quality input, not a conversion guarantee — whether clicks become opt-ins or sales still depends entirely on the funnel and offer the traffic lands on.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do I need to be an OLSP member to buy solo ads from Wayne Crowe?</summary>
        <p>No — OLSP Solo Ads can be purchased by non-members as a standalone traffic service. However, the ecosystem is designed to provide the most value to existing OLSP members who have Magick Link or Mega Link funnels in place. Non-members can direct solo ad traffic to their own opt-in pages or affiliate funnels. For non-members, the primary value is the traffic delivery itself; the integrated funnel alignment and commission structure are specifically OLSP-member benefits.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do OLSP Solo Ads compare to buying from a marketplace like Udimi?</summary>
        <p>The key difference is transparency versus ecosystem integration. On Udimi, you can see detailed metrics for individual vendors — including opt-in rate history, sales conversion data, and buyer reviews — before purchasing. This allows comparison shopping and risk reduction through pre-purchase due diligence. OLSP Solo Ads is a vendor-direct purchase from a single source; you rely on brand reputation, existing affiliate reviews (many of which carry financial incentives), and the training ecosystem rather than a marketplace rating system. Neither model guarantees results, but the transparency mechanisms differ substantially. For OLSP members already using Magick Link funnels, the ecosystem integration of OLSP Solo Ads provides a friction reduction that a marketplace vendor cannot match.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What do I need to have in place before buying solo ads?</summary>
        <p>At minimum: a live, tested opt-in page or funnel URL that is specifically relevant to the MMO/Biz Opp niche (to match the traffic's subscriber intent), and an email autoresponder with a follow-up sequence set up behind the opt-in. Solo ads deliver clicks to a URL — what happens after the click determines whether you recover your spend and build a profitable list. The vendor's own training emphasises this point: buying traffic without a solid offer and funnel in place is described even in OLSP-aligned content as a path to low ROI.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

